      <description>Video Materials
Now that we&amp;rsquo;ve learned some of the different looping constructs in Python, let&amp;rsquo;s work through a completed example to see how we can use loops to build more advanced programs.
Problem Statement For this example, we&amp;rsquo;d like to build a program that matches the following problem statement:
Write a program that will accept a series of integers from the terminal, one per line. It will continue to accept integers from the user until the user inputs 0.</description>
